    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I want to make sure my students don't just see one side as \"correct\" and the other as just being difficult. Looking at those two, would you say the procedural approach is a more legitimate way to interpret the law, or is the substantive approach just an inevitable part of a living Constitution?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
